Newfoundlanders see themselves?

08:11.560 --> 08:13.389
I mean, something seems
to be happening here

08:13.423 --> 08:20.810
as far as people here beginning
to value their own products,

08:20.845 --> 08:22.329
their own traditional food ways.

08:22.363 --> 08:24.055
Yeah.

08:24.089 --> 08:25.401
That's a big change,

08:25.435 --> 08:27.817
and it's something that
Jeremy Charles, for instance,

08:27.852 --> 08:29.578
has been doing
very, very, very successfully.

08:29.612 --> 08:31.165
How important is that?

08:31.200 --> 08:33.754
I think the one thing
that has kept people here

08:33.789 --> 08:35.515
in the wake
of the fisheries collapse...

08:35.549 --> 08:38.207
Like the fish moratorium
in 1992,

08:38.241 --> 08:39.519
so many people left.

08:39.553 --> 08:41.244
And what really
has kept people here

08:41.279 --> 08:42.763
is that sense of tradition.

08:42.798 --> 08:44.454
I think sometimes
there's this idea

08:44.489 --> 08:46.836
that tradition is static,
and that isn't necessarily true.

08:46.871 --> 08:48.037
Tradition is always
kind of changing

08:48.044 --> 08:50.012
in response to the environment.

08:50.046 --> 08:52.248
And people choose the things
that they're passionate about,

08:52.255 --> 08:54.119
and they find a way
to make that work.

08:54.154 --> 08:56.570
And I think Newfoundlanders
have always had that tradition

08:56.605 --> 08:59.021
of making do
and making things work

08:59.055 --> 09:00.678
in the situation where they are.

09:05.924 --> 09:07.754
